<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-29T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="616" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">352.3515/1: Circular telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to <gloss type="to">All American Consular
                                        Officers in Spain</gloss></hi><note n="70" xml:id="d616fn70">Sent also to the Embassy at Madrid as telegram No. 56, July 29,
                                    5 p.m.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-29T17:00:00-04:00">July 29, 1936—5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>At the request of the several governments you are authorized to
                                extend insofar as the circumstances permit your facilities for
                                protection <pb facs="0749" n="650" xml:id="pg_650"/> and if
                                necessary evacuation to the nationals of Argentina, Austria,
                                Belgium, Chile, Cuba, Finland, Panama, Sweden and Turkey.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>